TITLE: Defining TaxCategory Entity with TypeORM in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines the TaxCategory entity class for the Vendure application using TypeScript and TypeORM. The class specifies properties for the category name, a boolean flag for default status, custom fields, and relationships to associated ProductVariant and TaxRate entities. Dependencies include TypeORM decorators (@Column, @OneToMany) and types such as VendureEntity, HasCustomFields, and related entity classes. Input parameters include an optional deep-partial object for flexible instantiation, and the class outputs an entity instance with appropriate fields and ORM mappings; limitations depend on the custom field definitions and database schema.
